messages.message: Not sure, how many of you have read this paper (the portion relevant screenshoted below) -- instead of needing supervised training, if AI can learn reasoning as an emergent behavior from Reinforcement Learning -- a key question is -- can you create a mock simulation of complex task execution (in an enterprise setting) and have execution ability emerge from RL on large simulation? My guess is: browser execution by Anthropic and Operator by AI is an early example of that sort of AI.
